export default function Home (props) { let userName = props.user async function sendCmt () { // sends username, password from input server then creates s3 bucket in username and stores details on mongo const Comment = document.getElementById('cmt').value;// get username password and email // data to be sent in request to api includinb id of mongodb document let data = {Username: userName, Updatetype: '$set', Key2updt: 'Posts', Value2updt: Comment } // object containing fetch options for the put request let options = { method: 'PUT', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', }, body: JSON.stringify(data), } let postUrl = 'http://192.168.1.93:4001/postMsg' // post request using options object console.time("put response took"); let response = await fetch(postUrl, options) let convert = await response.json () console.timeEnd("put response took"); console.log("added comment updated document is:") console.log(convert) if ( response.status === 401 || response.status === 400){// handle not a match alert("your comment wasnt added try again") // Navigate("/signIn") //return false } else if ( response.status === 200){ // if password is a match return auth'd username console.log("pushed comment") alert("saved") //document.cookie = "authjwt="+convert.token; // store data in cookie //localStorage.setItem('jwt_token', convert.token) // Store JWT in storage //alert("Welcome to the club! Please setup your profile") //Navigate ("/profileSetup") } } return (
